  "text": "Strengths-This study began with a genome-wide approach in subjects with the most extreme BP values in the population, an approach that has enhanced power to detect genetic marker-on-trait association, even when the genotype contributes only modestly to total trait variation [CITATION_1] . Evidence for involvement of the SLC35F3 gene in hypertension then emerged from multiple lines of evidence: clinical, genetic, and biochemical.",
